---
import ProjectLayout from '../../layouts/ProjectLayout.astro';
const base = import.meta.env.BASE_URL.replace(/\/$/, '');
---
<ProjectLayout
  title="Peak-Hour Fleet Distribution at Special Events: Pride Parade Analysis"
  year="2024"
  category="Event Analysis · Mobility Management"
  tools={['Python', 'GeoPandas', 'Pandas', 'QGIS', 'Populus', 'Density Mapping']}
>

  <section class="proj-section">
    <h2 class="proj-section-title">Background</h2>
    <div class="proj-body">
      <p>
        Tel Aviv's Pride Parade is the city's largest annual street event, and for a few hours it
        upends transportation demand downtown. Riders cluster along the route while road closures
        cut other areas off from e-scooter access. This analysis mapped that mismatch during the
        parade's peak hour.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="proj-section">
    <h2 class="proj-section-title">Maps — Pride Parade Peak Hour</h2>
    <div class="proj-map-grid">
      <div>
        <img
          src={`${base}/maps/pride-distribution.jpg`}
          alt="Map of shared e-scooter distribution during Tel Aviv Pride Parade peak hour"
          class="proj-map"
          loading="lazy"
        />
        <p class="proj-map-caption">Vehicle fleet distribution at peak hour — Pride Parade 2024.</p>
      </div>
      <div>
        <img
          src={`${base}/maps/pride-density.jpg`}
          alt="Density map of shared e-scooter concentration during Pride Parade"
          class="proj-map"
          loading="lazy"
        />
        <p class="proj-map-caption">Vehicle density surface during parade peak hour.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="proj-section">
    <h2 class="proj-section-title">Methodology</h2>
    <ul class="proj-list">
      <li>Filtered real-time fleet feeds from <strong>Populus</strong> to the peak-hour window and built point-in-time snapshots with <strong>Python</strong> and <strong>Pandas</strong>.</li>
      <li>Joined vehicle locations to a spatial grid and municipal parking-restriction polygons using <strong>GeoPandas</strong>.</li>
      <li>Generated <strong>KDE</strong> density surfaces for vehicle supply and trip-origin demand, then visualized both in <strong>QGIS</strong> at matched scales.</li>
    </ul>
  </section>

  <section class="proj-section">
    <h2 class="proj-section-title">Results</h2>
    <div class="proj-body">
      <p>
        The maps exposed clear gaps between where scooters were parked and where riders needed them
        — including no-go zones created by parking restrictions with no compensating supply nearby.
        The findings fed directly into the city's pre-positioning talks with operators ahead of
        future events.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

</ProjectLayout>

<style>
  :global(.proj-list) {
    list-style: none;
    padding: 0;
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 10px;
    max-width: 68ch;
  }
  :global(.proj-list li) {
    font-size: 0.9rem;
    line-height: 1.7;
    color: #2A2A2A;
    padding-left: 1.2em;
    position: relative;
  }
  :global(.proj-list li::before) {
    content: '—';
    position: absolute;
    left: 0;
    color: #3D5E35;
    font-weight: 600;
  }
</style>
